dcterms:description: The Kuramoto-Sivashinsky system is widely used to simulate large-scale chaotic physical systems, providing a framework for testing predictive models in chaotic dynamics.

dcterms:creator: Y. Kuramoto
dcterms:description: An additional reference for the Kuramoto-Sivashinsky system, discussing diffusion-induced chaos in reaction systems, which is relevant for understanding chaotic dynamics.
